<p>I am using Jaspersoft Studio Community and Chart components.</p>  <p>I need to define javascript action for the series of my chart. I can do it through <strong>Hyperlink definition</strong>, like this:</p>  <pre><code>Hyperlink Reference Expression: "javascript:myfunction(" + $F{ID} + ")"; </code></pre>  <p>The result might look like this (one of the series):</p>  <pre><code>&lt;area shape="rect" coords="86,144,134,194" href="javascript:myfunction(123)" id="aui_3_4_0_1_1838"&gt; </code></pre>  <p>But it is bad habit to use javascript in <strong>href</strong> attribute, so is any way to define <strong>onclick</strong> attribute instead of <strong>href</strong> in Jaspersoft Studio?</p>